176
00:11:21,645 --> 00:11:28,636
And whereas the letter of Counselor Scott Polley raised various issues relating to the vote taken on significant municipal financial matters and the actions of the Medford City Council.

177
00:11:29,795 --> 00:11:59,078
And whereas, in light of the long-term absence of an appointed city solicitor in the city of Medford and the fact that the city's private legal counsel is a law firm hired by the mayor, and whereas the director of operations of the office of the state auditor responded to Councilor Scott Pelley's letter, that the state auditor would, quote, examine the issues raised in the letter if the examination of these issues had the approval of a majority vote of the city council and the mayor, as required by state statute, and whereas the fairest and most objective fashion to resolve the issues raised in Councilor Scott Pelley's letter is to have an outside agency address these issues,

178
00:11:59,878 --> 00:12:02,100
and determine the most appropriate way to address these issues.

179
00:12:02,140 --> 00:12:08,645
Now, therefore, we are resolved that the Medford City Council approve and authorize the Office of the State Auditor to examine the issues set forth in said letter.

180
00:12:08,765 --> 00:12:09,766
Councilor Scarpelli.

181
00:12:12,127 --> 00:12:13,048
Thank you, Mr. President.

