01:01:25,987 --> 01:01:27,728
They work for the mayor.

670
01:01:28,229 --> 01:01:33,092
And when I say I don't trust the departments, I speak with the rank and file.

671
01:01:34,173 --> 01:01:35,574
And they privately talk to me.

672
01:01:38,116 --> 01:01:42,059
And we can't use their names because they're afraid of what goes up here.

673
01:01:42,340 --> 01:01:45,682
That's not throwing fuel on a fire.

674
01:01:45,983 --> 01:01:47,023
You asked the question.

675
01:01:47,043 --> 01:01:51,227
You brought up the question why I simply didn't go to these department heads and talk to them.

676
01:01:52,788 --> 01:01:53,569
Because again,

677
01:01:54,946 --> 01:01:59,828
The key words in my resolution are transparency and accountability.

678
01:02:00,469 --> 01:02:15,476
So if I want something to be transparent, I'm going to bring it up here in front of all of these people so they all understand the process, not sit in a director's office that they can appease your agenda.

679
01:02:16,116 --> 01:02:17,196
Because that's what we're seeing.

680
01:02:18,657 --> 01:02:19,638
Because you said it yourself,

681
01:02:20,768 --> 01:02:23,949
You said it yourself, that was a very important meeting for the override.

682
01:02:24,349 --> 01:02:30,471
That was a very important meeting during the budget to get that approved because there was fear that teachers were gonna be laid off.

683
01:02:33,251 --> 01:02:34,272
Simply not the truth.

684
01:02:36,832 --> 01:02:44,775
So, this is a simple, simple resolution as I said.

685
01:02:45,675 --> 01:02:49,836
This is just to send this off to the auditor and get,

686
01:02:50,905 --> 01:03:05,790
a true indication of what the financial mismanagement that I see and others see, that we get the answers that are needed and required as we move forward, especially when you're talking about what you were asking for in November, when you talk about overrides.

687
01:03:05,871 --> 01:03:20,256
Because it's very important that we get the message out so everybody doesn't make a decision out of anger or lack of knowledge or lack of what was done during the budget season, because that's what it lends to.

688
01:03:21,482 --> 01:03:22,343
That's what it lends to.

689
01:03:23,944 --> 01:03:26,946
Say whatever you want, but that's what it lends to.

690
01:03:27,866 --> 01:03:30,508
And this is why this community is so divided.

691
01:03:31,488 --> 01:03:39,033
This isn't, this is just one council standing up to make sure that the whole community is listened to.

692
01:03:39,534 --> 01:03:43,356
Not the 200 people that showed up for meeting and they were gonna be inconvenienced.

693
01:03:43,776 --> 01:03:45,638
Because honestly, I know all of you.

694
01:03:46,218 --> 01:03:48,940
And I know you're very bright people and we've talked a lot

695
01:03:50,751 --> 01:04:07,845
And if I talked to you privately and I said, realistically, y'all given information about $9 million on a Friday, without talking to anybody, even okay, we talked to the directors, but then we go to move on a vote on a Tuesday.

696
01:04:09,066 --> 01:04:11,488
Truly, that is definitely not enough time.

697
01:04:11,768 --> 01:04:12,809
I've been doing this long enough.

698
01:04:13,310 --> 01:04:17,393
That's not enough time to get the answers that this community deserves.

699
01:04:19,195 --> 01:04:19,335
So,

700
01:04:22,711 --> 01:04:25,313
This is what was said tonight.

701
01:04:25,853 --> 01:04:31,957
Sure, this is the process of the council, and the process of the council, you went through with the letter of the law.

702
01:04:32,738 --> 01:04:35,460
You motioned it, you voted it, absolutely.

703
01:04:36,220 --> 01:04:48,489
But I will tell you, say what you want, Council Vance, we worked together, and the council's working together in the room right now, broke a rule that we can use against transparency and open dialogue.

704
01:04:48,709 --> 01:04:49,690
Never would have done that to you.

705
01:04:49,990 --> 01:04:50,911
You might have lost the vote,

706
01:04:52,142 --> 01:04:54,764
You might have lost the vote, but it was understood.

707
01:04:54,784 --> 01:04:59,167
And same here, hey, when I sit and I lose a vote, I take it and move on.

708
01:04:59,767 --> 01:05:02,990
But to be stymied, that's not acceptable.

709
01:05:03,590 --> 01:05:03,950
Thank you.

710
01:05:04,811 --> 01:05:05,231
Thank you.

711
01:05:05,251 --> 01:05:14,258
I'm not going to relitigate it, and I respect what you just said.

712
01:05:15,302 --> 01:05:19,044
There's some stuff that happened in summer 2020 that I felt similarly aggrieved by.

713
01:05:19,064 --> 01:05:21,965
I didn't write a letter about it.

714
01:05:22,746 --> 01:05:23,726
Vice President Collins.

715
01:05:34,032 --> 01:05:35,493
Sorry, there's just so much to talk about.

716
01:05:35,513 --> 01:05:37,694
You know what I mean?

717
01:05:41,336 --> 01:05:41,576
Thank you.

718
01:05:44,397 --> 01:05:50,679
You know, I think this is one of those issues where I think we really do agree in what we want.

719
01:05:50,699 --> 01:05:54,720
And we see it, we see what's happening differently.

720
01:05:56,260 --> 01:06:06,163
What really nettles me is we have so much, it's not like what we say, people in the community believe, because obviously that's not the case.

721
01:06:07,003 --> 01:06:10,884
But I think we, having one of these microphones is really powerful.

722
01:06:11,145 --> 01:06:12,365
It comes with a lot of influence.

723
01:06:13,700 --> 01:06:28,929
And I think every person behind this rail is in their way, in their different ways, really sensitive to the role that they occupy, the voice that they have, how people hear them, how they're framing the issues, how they're hearing the issues from the committee.

724
01:06:29,349 --> 01:06:33,452
I know that every counselor behind this rail is very sensitive to the type

725
01:06:34,509 --> 01:06:41,731
of leader and listener and speaker and representative that they are perceived to be by the community.

726
01:06:41,771 --> 01:06:57,877
And that's why it is so upsetting to me when behind this rail, we further narratives and binaries that I think are both not true, but actively harmful to our ability to come together and work together.

727
01:06:58,037 --> 01:07:01,738
For example, setting up a binary between

728
01:07:03,430 --> 01:07:15,333
talking about your assumptions and opinions as though they are fact in a city council meeting versus meeting with department heads who are duplicitous to further your own agenda.

729
01:07:16,153 --> 01:07:18,953
That binary does not exist.

730
01:07:19,053 --> 01:07:24,595
And I don't think it is helpful to put that forward as your two options.

731
01:07:24,815 --> 01:07:25,835
That's not what happens.

732
01:07:27,115 --> 01:07:28,015
That's not what happens.

733
01:07:29,356 --> 01:07:30,536
I also don't think it's helpful

734
01:07:33,584 --> 01:07:48,534
to set up a binary between winning a vote and being actively silenced, we've all been on the losing side of the vote.

735
01:07:49,575 --> 01:08:02,884
And whether we feel maligned by that or victimized by that, I don't think it's fair to how we talk about these issues to get to pick and choose when we're going to waive that as a flag.

736
01:08:03,772 --> 01:08:10,316
And it's not that I want to minimize the experience of having something that you ardently believe in and getting shot down.

737
01:08:10,336 --> 01:08:11,817
I know that sucks.

738
01:08:12,057 --> 01:08:16,840
I've been there many times, my first term especially.

739
01:08:17,360 --> 01:08:27,467
But I think it is deeply unhelpful to the community, to this body being able to function at what it's supposed to do for us to broadcast that our two options are

740
01:08:30,387 --> 01:08:36,849
be a winning vote for some nefarious agenda or be a stymied, silenced constituency.

741
01:08:37,369 --> 01:08:41,130
Because I think that, you know, we talk about that's why we're divided.

742
01:08:42,130 --> 01:08:44,751
There's nothing more dividing than being told we're divided.

743
01:08:46,091 --> 01:08:56,194
I wish that we came into these conversations not already mad at each other, but willing to say what's happening here and being willing to listen to the answers.

744
01:08:57,454 --> 01:08:59,335
We had a conversation with the finance director

745
01:09:00,401 --> 01:09:08,968
before the budget about free cash projections, what it's been in the past, what is projected to be, why free cash accumulates the way that it does.

746
01:09:09,448 --> 01:09:21,298
I don't think it's fair to residents to keep having this conversation about how our accumulation of free cash, which has now been put into funds where it can be used for purposes throughout the year.

747
01:09:21,318 --> 01:09:28,084
I don't think it's fair to the residents to keep talking about this like it was some scheme.

748
01:09:29,532 --> 01:09:36,378
I don't get why it's fair to the people of this city to keep beating a drum that misinforms people.

749
01:09:41,263 --> 01:09:42,364
It's okay if you disagree.

750
01:09:42,584 --> 01:09:44,205
I just wish that we were able to talk about it.

751
01:09:45,146 --> 01:09:45,506
That's all.

752
01:09:47,448 --> 01:09:48,129
Thank you.

753
01:09:48,329 --> 01:09:50,070
Vice President Collins, Councilor Kellyanne.

754
01:09:52,018 --> 01:09:55,400
I also feel like there are so many responses that I could give.

755
01:09:55,540 --> 01:09:58,602
It's really not possible to respond to everything.

756
01:09:58,622 --> 01:10:05,305
First of all, I was sad that your motion was Rule 21.

757
01:10:05,345 --> 01:10:06,425
I was going to vote for it then.

758
01:10:06,445 --> 01:10:09,287
I was also going to vote for it the week after when it was pulled.

759
01:10:10,447 --> 01:10:13,168
I also want to know the answer to these legal questions.

760
01:10:13,368 --> 01:10:25,710
I do not feel as sure as Councilor Tsang that I know exactly what that law states, and I would like an official legal opinion, and I look forward to what the Attorney General says.

761
01:10:27,531 --> 01:10:37,873
I also wish that, as a general rule, financial matters were brought to us earlier so that we were not under the gun and had to do things.

762
01:10:41,476 --> 01:10:44,718
So that is a situation that we are put in.

763
01:10:45,699 --> 01:10:59,928
And while it is accurate to say that some pink slips went out, some pink slips go out every year, and there would have been dozens and many dozens more pink slips if we had not passed what we passed.

764
01:11:01,229 --> 01:11:05,312
I think it's not accurate to say that it made no difference, right?

765
01:11:05,412 --> 01:11:11,176
It made a big difference to our schools, whether we voted that week or the next week.

766
01:11:12,577 --> 01:11:17,019
I don't like being, would I like another week or two to be able to look at these financial questions?

767
01:11:17,299 --> 01:11:18,200
You bet I would.

768
01:11:18,220 --> 01:11:29,445
I'm not the one putting these matters to the city council at the absolute last second so that we are forced to vote on them as fast as possible.

769
01:11:29,465 --> 01:11:30,066
I don't like that.

770
01:11:32,095 --> 01:11:40,101
I really wish that I had some miraculous way to know how the 60,000 people in Medford all think.

771
01:11:41,342 --> 01:11:45,646
I'm surprised to hear anyone say that they know how those 60,000 people all think.

772
01:11:46,726 --> 01:11:54,032
I also am really having a lot of trouble understanding how the, like,

773
01:11:56,963 --> 01:12:08,752
auditing the way that the overrides were passed because the overrides are a major problem, you know, that our community is not being listened to.

774
01:12:08,792 --> 01:12:16,077
This whole argument really, I'm really struggling with this because, you know, the overrides was a question of

775
01:12:16,257 --> 01:12:23,087
rule 21 and basically us being able to vote on them that week or not.

776
01:12:23,108 --> 01:12:26,593
I don't think there's any argument that rule 21 was

777
01:12:28,577 --> 01:12:33,999
suspended and that whether that was suspended in a way that was legally like okay or not okay.

778
01:12:34,019 --> 01:12:36,900
I think that simply is unfortunately what it is.

779
01:12:36,980 --> 01:12:40,342
Maybe you don't like the politics of it, but that was voted on properly.

780
01:12:40,762 --> 01:12:42,643
And then whether the whole community has listened to it.

781
01:12:42,843 --> 01:12:45,484
I mean, we're literally allowing the voters for the first time.

782
01:12:45,504 --> 01:12:47,264
We're allowing the voters to be listened to.

783
01:12:47,745 --> 01:12:50,746
We are allowing them to be listened to for the first time in decades.

784
01:12:50,846 --> 01:12:53,287
And I'm really struggling with this argument.

785
01:12:54,924 --> 01:13:07,454
or how putting overrides on the ballot so that the community can in fact be listened to by having a democratic vote where everyone can come to the ballot box, how that is not listening to the community.

786
01:13:07,494 --> 01:13:22,405
And I will also say that all the people, I mean, the wildly overwhelming support of people who came to that meeting and spoke in support of putting the overrides on the ballot, and we're yet being told that we aren't listening to the community.

787
01:13:22,445 --> 01:13:24,127
That's really struggling.

788
01:13:24,807 --> 01:13:38,999
with how that can be when number one, wildly overwhelming support from the community at the meeting where we discussed it, and number two, all we're doing is putting it on the ballot so that we can listen to the community.

789
01:13:39,639 --> 01:13:52,390
Now, finally, I wanna say that this particular matter, there is no deadline for whether we vote for an audit.

790
01:13:53,622 --> 01:14:01,310
And I am completely, do not understand what the heck we are auditing, because we are gonna audit everything.

791
01:14:01,650 --> 01:14:03,352
We're gonna audit financial mismanagement.

792
01:14:03,572 --> 01:14:09,498
We're gonna audit the management style of the council president, which I pretty much guarantee you the state auditor is not going to do.

793
01:14:09,518 --> 01:14:14,423
The number of things that have been mentioned that we are auditing, I have no idea.

794
01:14:15,103 --> 01:14:25,472
what this motion is here to say, and I am not gonna vote on a motion to have the state auditor come in and who knows, spend millions of dollars auditing, I don't know, any random thing.

795
01:14:26,313 --> 01:14:32,698
This is not a reasonable thing to vote in favor of.

796
01:14:35,741 --> 01:14:36,021
Thank you.

797
01:14:36,621 --> 01:14:37,082
Thank you.

798
01:14:37,262 --> 01:14:39,524
I wish that everyone would respect the councilor's right to speak.

799
01:14:40,979 --> 01:14:43,000
Any further discussion by members of the council?

800
01:14:43,040 --> 01:14:44,701
Mr. President, I just have one comment.

801
01:14:44,741 --> 01:14:45,881
Thank you, Mr. President.

802
01:14:46,361 --> 01:15:03,569
Just to expand on what Councilor Callahan mentioned about the process and how everybody was here that night and they were so excited about the override and giving the voice to the people first time voting on it.

803
01:15:04,429 --> 01:15:10,112
If you remember the conversation and if you remember the dialogue that was set forth in my motions,

804
01:15:11,598 --> 01:15:22,206
was the fact that we had a financial task force that we didn't see or understand how they got to that situation.

805
01:15:22,766 --> 01:15:34,495
We didn't see how they showed us why we need an override, what got us to that override, and what are we gonna do in the next steps to make sure that we don't need another override the following year.

806
01:15:34,535 --> 01:15:35,255
These are the questions.

807
01:15:35,696 --> 01:15:39,539
This is a transparent process that we were asking for that evening.

808
01:15:40,279 --> 01:15:42,740
And of course people came up and voted for it.

809
01:15:42,760 --> 01:15:46,541
And of course they want to be told that we should go on to vote.

810
01:15:46,801 --> 01:15:47,261
Sure.

811
01:15:48,342 --> 01:15:51,483
But you're not listening to the people that are right in front of you.

812
01:15:52,283 --> 01:15:56,545
As many of those people that came up and said, we're for it, thank you so much.

813
01:15:57,605 --> 01:16:00,046
You have the same amount of people that are telling you right now.

814
01:16:00,406 --> 01:16:01,606
You're not listening to them.

815
01:16:02,047 --> 01:16:02,947
But you're not hearing them.

816
01:16:04,619 --> 01:16:24,090
So I find it a little disturbing that the process of silencing or discussing or transparency or accountability would have come out in those meetings and discussions when we had the opportunity before the votes came out and understood, okay, the financial task force met.

817
01:16:25,034 --> 01:16:48,849
no minutes, no understanding how they got to where they did, but we're gonna come out with a $7.5 million override, a $30 million debt exclusion, which by the way, you're gonna be shocked when the firefighters come knocking pretty soon, and the understanding that not just a week later, we find $9 million more in free cash.

818
01:16:51,052 --> 01:17:01,986
That alone, if that doesn't open your eyes and say, well, geez, Councilor Scott Pelley, eliminate all the negative banter, eliminate one side or the other, geez, that's exactly what happened.

819
01:17:02,627 --> 01:17:06,051
And yeah, maybe we should look at that.

820
01:17:07,032 --> 01:17:10,893
Even though, Councilor Seng said it, you just said it, people came to that podium.

821
01:17:11,173 --> 01:17:12,534
Of course they were in favor of it.

822
01:17:13,234 --> 01:17:17,555
But the problem was the people that had questions weren't listened to.

823
01:17:18,435 --> 01:17:20,856
That's a lack of transparency and accountability, my friend.

824
01:17:21,176 --> 01:17:22,556
This is the problem we have.

825
01:17:23,937 --> 01:17:25,477
This is why we're here.

826
01:17:26,237 --> 01:17:31,219
So you might be confused in the verbiage that I'm sending the auditor, but let me simplify it.

827
01:17:31,519 --> 01:17:35,040
I'm asking the auditor, with our vote,

828
01:17:37,028 --> 01:17:41,029
to look at our city's finances, period.

829
01:17:42,309 --> 01:17:45,430
We'll move forward with the Attorney General after I speak with them tomorrow.

830
01:17:46,591 --> 01:17:47,791
Maybe they have something to share.

831
01:17:48,731 --> 01:17:58,454
But this isn't a very difficult, you can make this a convoluted resolution and be very confusing just because you wanna sign it, but it's a very, to everybody, it's a very simple process.

832
01:17:59,094 --> 01:18:05,596
My resolution states that we ask the state auditor by a city council vote and then the mayor's approval

833
01:18:05,976 --> 01:18:26,209
to come in and look at the city's finances because I question the process of millions of dollars in free cash and the process of how we got to certain votes when it comes to a financial task force that didn't have minutes to explain to the public what's happened to this community financially, period.

834
01:18:27,030 --> 01:18:27,390
Thank you.

835
01:18:27,710 --> 01:18:28,391
Vice President Collins.

836
01:18:34,482 --> 01:18:36,302
Hopefully this will be the last time I speak on this paper.

837
01:18:36,342 --> 01:18:37,943
I just wanted to note two things.

838
01:18:41,544 --> 01:18:45,045
I hear you that you wish there had been minutes coming out of the financial task force.

839
01:18:46,525 --> 01:18:54,327
You know, maybe the next time this is necessary, it'll be formed by committee instead of being a flexible ad hoc group.

840
01:18:55,401 --> 01:19:00,664
thing is that any decisions that came out of this task force were put to a vote in a public meeting.

841
01:19:00,724 --> 01:19:18,576
And I also think it's really relevant to note, I think it's a very critical distinction that any proposals came out that were discussed in the financial task force, of which I was a member, put forward to the city council, we approved them.

842
01:19:20,477 --> 01:19:22,799
Any residents who feel

843
01:19:25,712 --> 01:19:31,993
skeptical or uncomfortable or just disapproving of the proposals or of the process.

844
01:19:33,634 --> 01:19:34,134
What do you do?

845
01:19:34,254 --> 01:19:35,614
You go to the polls and you vote no.

846
01:19:38,095 --> 01:19:38,935
And that's the difference.

847
01:19:39,515 --> 01:19:40,495
You can do that.

848
01:19:40,875 --> 01:19:41,515
That's your right.

849
01:19:42,195 --> 01:19:42,796
That's your right.

850
01:19:43,716 --> 01:19:49,277
From now until the election, residents who happen to be in favor of the proposals

851
01:19:49,813 --> 01:19:51,474
we'll be making the case for them.

852
01:19:52,154 --> 01:19:54,875
There will be a lot of answers coming out.

853
01:19:55,115 --> 01:19:58,777
That's the process, because this is a thing that everybody gets to vote yes or no on.

854
01:19:59,937 --> 01:20:05,119
We will not be making that case from the podium because this is a matter that's going to be voted on, that would be improper.

855
01:20:05,979 --> 01:20:07,900
But this information, this case will be made.

856
01:20:08,380 --> 01:20:15,403
We will have a chance to discuss and debate the answer to those questions by we, I mean the community, in the community.

857
01:20:18,183 --> 01:20:19,984
Let's see if I can remember the second point I was going to make.

858
01:20:20,004 --> 01:20:27,646
I might have lost it.

859
01:20:27,706 --> 01:20:28,666
It's been a long day.

860
01:20:29,887 --> 01:20:30,707
We'll come back to you.

861
01:20:30,887 --> 01:20:31,127
Thanks.

862
01:20:31,707 --> 01:20:33,248
Any further comments by members of the council?

